    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>This day I received your favour of 19<hi rend="superscript">th.</hi> ultimo, hope
                    you will have got my last on your arrival at London; yours for <persName ref="pe0100">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Freebairn</persName> was sent
                    off immediately, the postage was paid</p>
                <p>I shall endeavour to get the East Coast as well supplied for you as possible, can
                    recollect none further North, than what <persName ref="pe0565">Adair</persName>
                    has done, which can be depended on unless <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0247">M<hi rend="superscript">r.</hi> Mackenzie's Survey of the
                            Coast</title>
                    </bibl>
                    <add place="above">which last has not yet appeared</add>, if you have not <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0149">
                            <hi rend="underline">Adairs Coast
                                Maps</hi>
                        </title>
                    </bibl>, I will try to provide a Copy for you.</p>
                <p>So soon as <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0136">the Antiquities of
                            Stirlingshire with the Map</title>
                    </bibl> is published I shall beg your
                    Acceptance of it; as also <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0176">the History
                            of Glasgow with a plan</title>
                    </bibl> &amp; <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0142">Sir David Lindsay's Works</title>
                    </bibl> are by me
                    for you there shall be sent to <persName ref="pe0026">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> White's</persName> Care at <placeName ref="pl0699">London</placeName>, with these you will receive a new <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0144"> Plan of Dundee</title>
                    </bibl>: there
                    is a proposal of a Survey of <placeName ref="pl0733">Angusshire</placeName>
                    shortly to be begun by the same hand, one <persName ref="pe0566">Crawford</persName> a Young man, it's thought he will do the Antiquities
                        &amp;<hi rend="superscript">c.</hi> on a separate sheet from the Map</p>
                <p>I shall soon write you again &amp; am</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Dear Sir <lb/>Your most obed<hi rend="superscript">t.</hi> Serv<hi rend="superscript">t.</hi>
                    </salute>
                    <signed>
                        <persName ref="pe0228">GPaton</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName ref="pl0696">Custom house Edinburgh</placeName>
                    <lb/>4 April 1777.</dateline>
            </div>
